tags.note: No motorized boats at this launch. Hand-carried boats only.

tags.description: Offers 16 acres of prime parkland located in the heart of the city. It has 4 lit tennis courts, an all-weather lit multipurpose synthetic turf field, a lit baseball field, a multipurpose field, a soccer field and a quarter mile track.
tags.name: Evergreen Playfield

tags.description: The park is a 4.72 acres and includes a gazebo, lending library, paved walking trails, play equipment, monument, picnic and natural areas. The all-volunteer built trail travels around the entire circumference of the park.
tags.name: Matt Hirvela Bicentennial Park

tags.description: This park includes picnic tables, benches, play equipment, and walking trails. It was originally named "Larry Egbert Park" after an MLT Firefighter who was killed in the early 1970s. It was changed in the mid 1980s to honor all firefighters.
tags.name: Firefighters Memorial Park

tags.description: Located adjacent to the city's iconic water tower. Features picnic tables, benches, a climbing rock, horseshoe pits, a "little free library", and paved walking trails. A great place to take a picnic lunch, listen to birds sing, and relax.
tags.name: Jack Long Park

tags.description: Forest Crest Playfield is a 5 acre youth sport field complex.  It includes 2 small baseball fields and a T-ball field, which converts to a youth soccer field in the fall.
tags.name: Forest Crest Playfield
